<design_info><![CDATA[Snotlings don't cause Goblins to Panic, both don't Panic Orcs, all 3 don't Panic Trolls.
All Goblins fear Elves not outnumbered 2:1. Night Goblins hate Dwarves.
If any Orc unit of 20+ is in HtH you get +1, or if Fleeing -1 Power Dice.
Animosity: In turn, roll a D6 for every Orc and Goblin unit at start of your turn: 1 = Shoot or charge friendly unit if possible (Goblins don't charge Orcs); 2-5 = Nothing happens; 6 = Moves towards nearest enemy at normal rate, count as charging if touching
Waaagh: General must be alive and not fleeing. Declare before rolling for Animosity. General's unit and Black Orcs count as rolling 6 for Animosity. Orcs add rank bonus to Animosity test. Goblins also, but only +1 at best. On a roll of 1 a unit Squabbles and suffers D6 Wounds (no armour save).]]></design_info>
